Please select the correct answer from options A, B, C, and D.
Question: In the AB magnitude system, a zeroth magnitude corresponds to a flux density of 3631 Jansky (Jy). What is the unit Jy in terms of the International System of Units?
Options:
A. 10^{-26} Js^{-1} m^{-2} sr^{-1} nm^{-1}
B. 10^{-26} Js^{-1}m^{-2}Hz^{-1}
C. 10^{-26} Js^{-1}m^{-2}nm^{-1}
D. 10^{-26} Jsm^{-2} sr^{-1} nm^{-1}
Reference knowledge:
Is a non-SI unit of spectral radiance or irradiance, equivalent to 10^{−26} watts per square meter per hertz.
